Nigerian Aviation Handling Company (NAHCO) Plc has secured renewal for ground handling agreement between it and four international carriers. Head, Corporate Communications, Nigerian Aviation Handling Company (NAHCO) Plc, Mr. Samuel Akinrinmade said the renewal deals were evidence of the dominance of the company as aviation logistics services provider and its satisfactory services to its clients over the years. According to him, Virgin Atlantic and Delta Airlines have renewed their Lagos contracts with NAHCO while Air France/Royal Dutch pitched tents with the company for its operations in Lagos, Abuja, and Port Harcourt. Also, Ethiopian Airlines  renewed its contracts with the company. NAHCO and Ethiopian Airlines have signed a new contract for the provision of warehousing services for the Airline’s Lagos operations.   Firm urges in-country cloud services hosting     West Africa’s food economy to hit $480b by 2030     ‘We approved, but have no records of $195m Deep Blue…   The company has also won the Qatar Airways’ Freighter and warehousing contracts for Kano and Port Harcourt. NAHCO, which handles most of the foreign airlines operating in the country, recently announced the signing of Qatar Airways handling for Kano and Port Harcourt. The Executive Director, Commercial and Business Development, Prince Saheed Lasisi, added: “We are pleased with the patronage of our valued clients. We appreciate our ever-supporting board and management and the contributions of our hardworking and dedicated staff”. He assured on plans to consolidate NAHCO leadership in the industry and the sustenance of the culture of excellence.